column5: If yer thinking for getting out one last time this would be the weekend to do it. I hear it's supposed to be 12 on Saturday and 13 on Sunday. Last week of November?????? Whatever.....  Sadly I'm tied up at work Saturday.  Good Luck to everyone who's gonna give it a go!
Thanks Jeff!!
You bet Jef.  We will be out there on the bay.  I am in some kinda fall funk, haven't caught a fish since mid-late sept.  Hope this weekend is the one!
Taking Christmas orders for bucktails yet Jef ??

i bet the bay of quinte or the lower niagara will be a parking lot.  Who wouldn't want to take advantage of this weekend.  oh wait me,  me and the wife are in a wedding this weekend.  good luck and enjoy it.  it will be your last nice weekend.

Sure am Jim. Drop me a line with the colors!  And Raf, you keep fishin' them big waters and that's what yer gonna get. But just remember, when you least expect it-expect it. That big fat girl will show herself sonner or later!
well I was suposed to go out with dad right now but he canciled on me so I am taking family time I guess it means I am in need of getting out Saturday and Sunday
those r nice fishing tempatures i will have to try to get out then.     jordan
Finally it is going to be a nice weekend. With the water being gin clear probally not gonna hit any tribs maybe try for some daytime walleye. Good luck everyone
Looks like it will be a great weekend, I plan to hit the gin clear tribs anyways!  Its stealth mode time thats for sure
Well...with my boat dropped off for it's trade in yesterday..guess I have no excuse now not to get my firewood split and stacked ...so I have wood for next winter.
Thinking about pulling an all nighter - Saturday night at the docks of Tip of the Bay and Sunday morning out on the reach. Gotta get me one of those fat girls!   Will report when I get back   Don
Go get'm Don. We caught ours right beside the freighter ! LOL

Wayne - I read in your post that you were down at the docks at tip of the bay - wish I knew - I was staying at Picton Harbour Inn - should have stopped in for a hot coffee or a cold pepsi. Did you have any luck off of the docks at night?   Don
Heading up to Gracefield tomorrow for a long weekend of chasing 'skis and pike. Yeah baby!
yup, this week-end is it for me.  One more shot at the upper before I pack'er in

thinki we might head down very early sunday morn for the day might be my last chance,the weather will at least be on our side,but ya it will prob,be real busy....i wont know till sat night if i go or not,i might still have 1 more chance to beat my PB from last weekend of 13.3lbs......
I plan on fishing alot this weekend...fri, sat, sun...total of about 25 hours of fishing...can't wait......LOL
Hey Mike, give me a shout if you're looking for company. I still owe you for the coffee and timbits from the last time out! -Brian
You in the same boat as me Wayne.You have to do your chores and please the wife.

Yes Mike...I have to do chores but only because I like to be warm in my shop...not to please the wife! LOL  She'll be splitting wood right beside me as always...good exercise and a tractor/hydraulic splitter isn't something you should be doing without a partner...just like fishing.
